<subSubSection id="4C99C4EACB7724708A16589EA9B572B0" pageId="null" pageNumber="908" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="854BE41B939FA91A7AFD80BA7B5FA467" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Echte Moorbeere</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="347F8AACBA491A597D95674159C9580D" pageId="null" pageNumber="908" type="description">
<paragraph id="9FF6E8AA33FF5D03091F0CF14D4EBD7C" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">
Unterscheidet sich durch folgende Merkmale von 
<taxonomicName id="66A860D3CA3D7DBCE11E6791F29BC512" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Vaccinium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="null" pageNumber="908" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gaultherioides">
<emphasis id="014000BC7156B6D07DD3B3052904516F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">V. gaultherioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 3): 
<emphasis id="2D3F010194E50CB78C54D95666AE377D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">
20-50 cm hoch; 
<normalizedToken id="5E75D0DD579F38977284092180D7C514" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
oft 
<normalizedToken id="5DBC7AD2E0648C13427C404967EC7ED4" originalValue="über" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">ueber</normalizedToken>
1 cm breit
</emphasis>
, mit der 
<normalizedToken id="6F1A823753DFB639B020C6D4F02D85F4" originalValue="größten" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">groessten</normalizedToken>
Breite oft in der Mitte, 
<normalizedToken id="B4BAB3D90724D5676B035448410D9F33" originalValue="dünn" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">duenn</normalizedToken>
, Rand kaum verdickt; 
<emphasis id="0764C614CD070E6BB5CEDFFDEEA7241F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">
<normalizedToken id="28530EF3FD27F54233B8EB3111CD405E" originalValue="Blüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Blueten</normalizedToken>
zu 2-3 beisammen
</emphasis>
(seltener einzeln), 
<emphasis id="03AB0950F8EB703AABE869D6ECAABCBD" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">auf 3-10 mm langen Stielen</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B5E0DC067FE26253F1B44D61CAF84215" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">
Stiele meist 
<normalizedToken id="29C898A01A4A5621381D1B22D6316E66" originalValue="länger" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">laenger</normalizedToken>
als die 
<normalizedToken id="703A71223DB2969CD5FEE5D487504EAA" originalValue="Blüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Blueten</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
). - 
<normalizedToken id="656AB6CC94EE9F92E7CB788238FBD03C" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: 
<normalizedToken id="D3660E0601E593A44ADC7EEA1E3A84E1" originalValue="Früher" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Frueher</normalizedToken>
Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0461E5C184DC72102590FDEF8B05A4C8" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">
<emphasis id="A2B9EB0932551AAC8EDF7CD60D4F920E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="D7DAE38FC59BCAC8EF0BD6544E64419F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">48:</emphasis>
Material aus 
<normalizedToken id="D67114682B98A1F0629DC6A815B4D57C" originalValue="Dänemark" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Daenemark</normalizedToken>
(Hagerup 1933), aus Island (
<normalizedToken id="5F911C48968DE9B0BFD1F24E0F6564C6" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Loeve</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="5DBCF2F548C34FE2DE224F002A496612" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Loeve</normalizedToken>
1956b), aus Nordeuropa (Rousi 1966Rousi 1967), aus Nordsibirien (Sokolovskaya und Strelkova 1960), aus Nordamerika (
<normalizedToken id="63F591C1495CFF24669A8F127A0C70DF" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Loeve</normalizedToken>
und Solbrig 1964a, 
<normalizedToken id="BA3FA330A3C48571C3146D658BB51343" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Loeve</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="A4447A3BA77FC511B99B7E7203E14917" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Loeve</normalizedToken>
1965), aus Kanada (Hedberg 1967).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B9FF7BBADB4AC04CE08A793C2F38BA3F" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">
<emphasis id="7D9516EDFBCCEC9A5F1FC10DE71445D8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin und montan, selten subalpin. Nasse, saure, 
<normalizedToken id="D4D164366B4ADE345D9E576ACD5A8863" originalValue="nährstoffarme" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">naehrstoffarme</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="AFDD8374ED25894B1F46439A6BF2FB3E" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Boeden</normalizedToken>
. Moore.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F232DD8D650E0A45FFA4EB96356D03F6" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">
<emphasis id="A5DF7F259733E2C27406D062BDB3CA55" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Verbreitung. Eurosibirisch-nordamerikanische Pflanze:</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="9C96DC8B93DEDD4DC1279E0BC2DFF424" originalValue="Nordwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Nordwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis in das zirkumpolare Verbreitungsgebiet von 
<taxonomicName id="E51D71468E3B55F04C5285D3C7947614" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Vaccinium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="null" pageNumber="908" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gaultherioides">
<emphasis id="E72BD7EF5B407A244E8B67451168813E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">V. gaultherioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 3) bis ca. 60° NB; 
<normalizedToken id="8AAE2926BAFF2EC63784633ED74E3525" originalValue="südwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">suedwaerts</normalizedToken>
in Eurasien bis 
<normalizedToken id="8B12AAD5DBC1AF063D6F121F4D012640" originalValue="ungefähr" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">ungefaehr</normalizedToken>
an den 
<normalizedToken id="FA121B1E3BBEA37F6DEFBCB801DCF963" originalValue="Südrand" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Suedrand</normalizedToken>
des Verbreitungsgebiets von 
<taxonomicName id="010A2C892B5E64F313B8A5A4BAB74C96" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Vaccinium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="null" pageNumber="908" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gaultherioides">
<emphasis id="22F91B74B73D5A556BA8A71D8794E62D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">V. gaultherioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, innerhalb dieses Gebiets in den tieferen Lagen; in Nordamerika 
<normalizedToken id="9C8E9EBAAE78E613735927875751AB30" originalValue="südwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">suedwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Kalifornien und Utah. - Im Gebiet verbreitet, nicht 
<normalizedToken id="02FAD822CEEA22D41288AD38B4982E6F" originalValue="häufig" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">haeufig</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED685313DE65C41EFFC8283BA8C9C1C9" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">
<emphasis id="484292829D14CB96885C5F10FA97D379" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">Bemerkungen.</emphasis>
Siehe unter 
<taxonomicName id="ECBA293A0A8B67C5D230C9B11F950984" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Vaccinium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="null" pageNumber="908" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gaultherioides">
<emphasis id="3A33D9DA6C323D9C464D8C5640E5FD91" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="908">V. gaultherioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 3).
</paragraph>
